HEADWORD: Pardonableness
<hw>Par"don*a*ble*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of
being pardonable; <as>as, the <ex>pardonableness</ex> of sin</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

